==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epsom salt
<hw>Ep"som salt`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Sulphate of magnesia having
cathartic qualities; -- originally prepared by boiling down the mineral
waters at <etsep>Epsom</etsep>, England, -- whence the name; afterwards
prepared from sea water; but now from certain minerals, as from
siliceous hydrate of magnesia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

